comment: Uh, what a greasy affair! This little bun was a sweet and tasty little thing, but there was liquid butter everywhere!

You're actually looking at the best cinnamon bun in Oslo tested for cinnanom! The bun has a lovely optic, the perfect amount of cinnamon worked into the dough with a nice level of sweetness. Also, it has a juicy core in the center. With the price of 46 NOK definitely one of the more expensive ones, but it's worth it!
Could be the winner of Norway’s next cinnamon bun model, but it does not convince for it’s level of cinnamon taste. Not very sweet, but a very noticable note of cardamom.
What a cutie. Convinces with a good level of sweetness, but there could be more cinnamon for our taste. How could you not give it a shot for that price?

If you ever decide to travel with the famous Bergensbanen between Oslo and Bergen, you’ll most certainly stumble over this cinnamon bun in the train’s cafe! It’s a good bun - eating it while the beautiful landscape passes by on the outside makes it a very unique experience.

For that price, it is a fine cinnamon bun. While it is very dough-y on the inside, it is a bit dryer on the outside. I’m quoting the second tester for this bun: “It feels like chewing on raw dough with cinnamon” - wow, he must have had a sleepless night or something. Also, sweet tongues need to be strong: it has a weak taste of cinnamon and isn’t that sweet either.
Definitely a 10/10 if we’d be looking for cardamom buns. This pastry has almost no cinnamon taste and isn’t on the sweet side either. Looks nice, though!
